P_HTM[7692]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[7693]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7694]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi rāhula, dhammā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**“What do you think, Rāhula? Are thoughts permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[7695]="*“Aniccā, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7696]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if they're impermanent, are they suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[7697]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7698]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if they're impermanent, suffering, and perishable, are they fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[7699]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[7700]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7701]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi rāhula, manoviññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**“What do you think, Rāhula? Is mind consciousness permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[7702]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7703]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[7704]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7705]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[7706]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[7707]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7708]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi rāhula, manosamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**“What do you think, Rāhula? Is mind contact permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[7709]="*“Anicco, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7710]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[7711]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7712]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[7713]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[7714]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7715]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[7716]="*yamidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ, tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Anything included in feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness that arises conditioned by mind contact: is that permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[7717]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7718]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[7719]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7720]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[7721]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[7722]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[7723]="*“Evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmiṃ nibbindati, rūpesu nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇe nibbindati, cakkhusamphasse nibbindati, yamidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ tasmimpi nibbindati.**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they grow disillusioned with anything included in feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness that arises conditioned by eye contact.*";
P_HTM[7724]="*Sotasmiṃ nibbindati, saddesu nibbindati … pe …**They grow disillusioned with the ear …*";
P_HTM[7725]="*ghānasmiṃ nibbindati, gandhesu nibbindati …**nose …*";
P_HTM[7726]="*jivhāya nibbindati, rasesu nibbindati …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[7727]="*kāyasmiṃ nibbindati, phoṭṭhabbesu nibbindati …**body …*";
P_HTM[7728]="*manasmiṃ nibbindati, dhammesu nibbindati, manoviññāṇe nibbindati, manosamphasse nibbindati, yamidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ tasmimpi nibbindati.**mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact. And they grow disillusioned with anything included in feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness that arises conditioned by mind contact.*";
P_HTM[7729]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[7730]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[7731]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7732]="*Attamano āyasmā rāhulo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Rāhula was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7733]="*Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne āyasmato rāhulassa anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimucci.**And while this discourse was being spoken, Rāhula’s mind was freed from defilements by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[7734]="*Tāsañca anekānaṃ devatāsahassānaṃ virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi:**And the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in those thousands of deities:*";
P_HTM[7735]="*“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti.**“Everything that has a beginning has an end.”*";
P_HTM[7736]="*Cūḷarāhulovādasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7737]="*148. Chachakkasutta**Six By Six*";
P_HTM[7738]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7739]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7740]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[7741]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[7742]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7743]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7744]="*“dhammaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsessāmi, yadidaṃ—**“Mendicants, I shall teach you the Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And I shall reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure, namely,*";
P_HTM[7745]="*cha chakkāni.**the six sets of six.*";
P_HTM[7746]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[7747]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7748]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7749]="*“Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbāni, cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbāni, cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā, cha phassakāyā veditabbā, cha vedanākāyā veditabbā, cha taṇhākāyā veditabbā.**“The six interior sense fields should be understood. The six exterior sense fields should be understood. The six classes of consciousness should be understood. The six classes of contact should be understood. The six classes of feeling should be understood. The six classes of craving should be understood.*";
P_HTM[7750]="*‘Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—**‘The six interior sense fields should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7751]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[7752]="*Cakkhāyatanaṃ, sotāyatanaṃ, ghānāyatanaṃ, jivhāyatanaṃ, kāyāyatanaṃ, manāyatanaṃ.**There are the sense fields of the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind.*";
P_HTM[7753]="*‘Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—**‘The six interior sense fields should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7754]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[7755]="*Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ chakkaṃ. (1)**This is the first set of six.*";
P_HTM[7756]="*‘Cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—**‘The six exterior sense fields should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7757]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[7758]="*Rūpāyatanaṃ, saddāyatanaṃ, gandhāyatanaṃ, rasāyatanaṃ, phoṭṭhabbāyatanaṃ, dhammāyatanaṃ.**There are the sense fields of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts.*";
P_HTM[7759]="*‘Cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—**‘The six exterior sense fields should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7760]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[7761]="*Idaṃ dutiyaṃ chakkaṃ. (2)**This is the second set of six.*";
P_HTM[7762]="*‘Cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā’ti—**‘The six classes of consciousness should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7763]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[7764]="*Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ,**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights.*";
P_HTM[7765]="*sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ,**Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds.*";
P_HTM[7766]="*ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ,**Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells.*";
P_HTM[7767]="*jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ,**Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes.*";
P_HTM[7768]="*kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ,**Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches.*";
P_HTM[7769]="*manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ.**Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts.*";
P_HTM[7770]="*‘Cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā’ti—**‘The six classes of consciousness should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7771]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[7772]="*Idaṃ tatiyaṃ chakkaṃ. (3)**This is the third set of six.*";
P_HTM[7773]="*‘Cha phassakāyā veditabbā’ti—**‘The six classes of contact should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7774]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[7775]="*Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso;**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[7776]="*sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso;**Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[7777]="*ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso;**Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[7778]="*jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso;**Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[7779]="*kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso;**Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[7780]="*manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso.**Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[7781]="*‘Cha phassakāyā veditabbā’ti—**‘The six classes of contact should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7782]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[7783]="*Idaṃ catutthaṃ chakkaṃ. (4)**This is the fourth set of six.*";
P_HTM[7784]="*‘Cha vedanākāyā veditabbā’ti—**‘The six classes of feeling should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7785]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[7786]="*Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā;**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[7787]="*sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā;**Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[7788]="*ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā;**Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[7789]="*jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā;**Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[7790]="*kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā;**Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[7791]="*manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā.**Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[7792]="*‘Cha vedanākāyā veditabbā’ti—**‘The six classes of feeling should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7793]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[7794]="*Idaṃ pañcamaṃ chakkaṃ. (5)**This is the fifth set of six.*";
P_HTM[7795]="*‘Cha taṇhākāyā veditabbā’ti—**‘The six classes of craving should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7796]="*iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ?**That’s what I said, but why did I say it?*";
P_HTM[7797]="*Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā, vedanāpaccayā taṇhā;**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling. Feeling is a condition for craving.*";
P_HTM[7798]="*sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Ear consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7799]="*ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ …**Nose consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7800]="*jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ …**Tongue consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7801]="*kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ …**Body consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7802]="*manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā, vedanāpaccayā taṇhā.**Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling. Feeling is a condition for craving.*";
P_HTM[7803]="*‘Cha taṇhākāyā veditabbā’ti—**‘The six classes of craving should be understood.’*";
P_HTM[7804]="*iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ.**That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.*";
P_HTM[7805]="*Idaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ chakkaṃ. (6)**This is the sixth set of six.*";
P_HTM[7806]="*‘Cakkhu attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**If anyone says, ‘the eye is self,’ that is not tenable.*";
P_HTM[7807]="*Cakkhussa uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.**The arising and vanishing of the eye is evident,*";
P_HTM[7808]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.**so it would follow that one’s self arises and vanishes.*";
P_HTM[7809]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:**That’s why it’s not tenable to claim that*";
P_HTM[7810]="*‘cakkhu attā’ti yo vadeyya.**the eye is self.*";
P_HTM[7811]="*Iti cakkhu anattā.**So the eye is not self.*";
P_HTM[7812]="*‘Rūpā attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**If anyone says, ‘sights are self,’ that is not tenable.*";
P_HTM[7813]="*Rūpānaṃ uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.**The arising and vanishing of sights is evident,*";
P_HTM[7814]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.**so it would follow that one’s self arises and vanishes.*";
P_HTM[7815]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:**That’s why it’s not tenable to claim that*";
P_HTM[7816]="*‘rūpā attā’ti yo vadeyya.**sights are self.*";
P_HTM[7817]="*Iti cakkhu anattā, rūpā anattā.**So the eye is not self and sights are not self.*";
P_HTM[7818]="*‘Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**If anyone says, ‘eye consciousness is self,’ that is not tenable.*";
P_HTM[7819]="*Cakkhuviññāṇassa uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.**The arising and vanishing of eye consciousness is evident,*";
P_HTM[7820]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.**so it would follow that one’s self arises and vanishes.*";
P_HTM[7821]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:**That’s why it’s not tenable to claim that*";
P_HTM[7822]="*‘cakkhuviññāṇaṃ attā’ti yo vadeyya.**eye consciousness is self.*";
P_HTM[7823]="*Iti cakkhu anattā, rūpā anattā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ anattā.**So the eye, sights, and eye consciousness are not self.*";
P_HTM[7824]="*‘Cakkhusamphasso attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**If anyone says, ‘eye contact is self,’ that is not tenable.*";
P_HTM[7825]="*Cakkhusamphassassa uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.**The arising and vanishing of eye contact is evident,*";
P_HTM[7826]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.**so it would follow that one’s self arises and vanishes.*";
P_HTM[7827]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:**That’s why it’s not tenable to claim that*";
P_HTM[7828]="*‘cakkhusamphasso attā’ti yo vadeyya.**eye contact is self.*";
P_HTM[7829]="*Iti cakkhu anattā, rūpā anattā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ anattā, cakkhusamphasso anattā.**So the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact are not self.*";
P_HTM[7830]="*‘Vedanā attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**If anyone says, ‘feeling is self,’ that is not tenable.*";
P_HTM[7831]="*Vedanāya uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.**The arising and vanishing of feeling is evident,*";
P_HTM[7832]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.**so it would follow that one’s self arises and vanishes.*";
P_HTM[7833]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:**That’s why it’s not tenable to claim that*";
P_HTM[7834]="*‘vedanā attā’ti yo vadeyya.**feeling is self.*";
P_HTM[7835]="*Iti cakkhu anattā, rūpā anattā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ anattā, cakkhusamphasso anattā, vedanā anattā.**So the eye, sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, and feeling are not self.*";
P_HTM[7836]="*‘Taṇhā attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**If anyone says, ‘craving is self,’ that is not tenable.*";
P_HTM[7837]="*Taṇhāya uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.**The arising and vanishing of craving is evident,*";
P_HTM[7838]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.**so it would follow that one’s self arises and vanishes.*";
P_HTM[7839]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:**That’s why it’s not tenable to claim that*";
P_HTM[7840]="*‘taṇhā attā’ti yo vadeyya.**craving is self.*";
P_HTM[7841]="*Iti cakkhu anattā, rūpā anattā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ anattā, cakkhusamphasso anattā, vedanā anattā, taṇhā anattā.**So the eye, sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, feeling, and craving are not self.*";
P_HTM[7842]="*‘Sotaṃ attā’ti yo vadeyya … pe …**If anyone says, ‘the ear is self’ …*";
P_HTM[7843]="*‘ghānaṃ attā’ti yo vadeyya … pe …**‘the nose is self’ …*";
P_HTM[7844]="*‘jivhā attā’ti yo vadeyya … pe …**‘the tongue is self’ …*";
P_HTM[7845]="*‘kāyo attā’ti yo vadeyya … pe …**‘the body is self’ …*";
P_HTM[7846]="*‘mano attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**‘the mind is self,’ that is not tenable.*";
P_HTM[7847]="*Manassa uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.**The arising and vanishing of the mind is evident,*";
P_HTM[7848]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.**so it would follow that one’s self arises and vanishes.*";
P_HTM[7849]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:**That’s why it’s not tenable to claim that*";
P_HTM[7850]="*‘mano attā’ti yo vadeyya.**the mind is self.*";
P_HTM[7851]="*Iti mano anattā.**So the mind is not self.*";
P_HTM[7852]="*‘Dhammā attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**If anyone says, ‘thoughts are self’ …*";
P_HTM[7853]="*Dhammānaṃ uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.* **";
P_HTM[7854]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7855]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:* **";
P_HTM[7856]="*‘dhammā attā’ti yo vadeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7857]="*Iti mano anattā, dhammā anattā.* **";
P_HTM[7858]="*‘Manoviññāṇaṃ attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**‘mind consciousness is self’ …*";
P_HTM[7859]="*Manoviññāṇassa uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.* **";
P_HTM[7860]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7861]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:* **";
P_HTM[7862]="*‘manoviññāṇaṃ attā’ti yo vadeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7863]="*Iti mano anattā, dhammā anattā, manoviññāṇaṃ anattā.* **";
P_HTM[7864]="*‘Manosamphasso attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**‘mind contact is self’ …*";
P_HTM[7865]="*Manosamphassassa uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.* **";
P_HTM[7866]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7867]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:* **";
P_HTM[7868]="*‘manosamphasso attā’ti yo vadeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7869]="*Iti mano anattā, dhammā anattā, manoviññāṇaṃ anattā, manosamphasso anattā.* **";
P_HTM[7870]="*‘Vedanā attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**‘feeling is self’ …*";
P_HTM[7871]="*Vedanāya uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.* **";
P_HTM[7872]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[7873]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:* **";
P_HTM[7874]="*‘vedanā attā’ti yo vadeyya.* **";
P_HTM[7875]="*Iti mano anattā, dhammā anattā, manoviññāṇaṃ anattā, manosamphasso anattā, vedanā anattā.* **";
P_HTM[7876]="*‘Taṇhā attā’ti yo vadeyya taṃ na upapajjati.**‘craving is self,’ that is not tenable.*";
P_HTM[7877]="*Taṇhāya uppādopi vayopi paññāyati.**The arising and vanishing of craving is evident,*";
P_HTM[7878]="*Yassa kho pana uppādopi vayopi paññāyati, ‘attā me uppajjati ca veti cā’ti iccassa evamāgataṃ hoti.**so it would follow that one’s self arises and vanishes.*";
P_HTM[7879]="*Tasmā taṃ na upapajjati:**That’s why it’s not tenable to claim that*";
P_HTM[7880]="*‘taṇhā attā’ti yo vadeyya.**craving is self.*";
P_HTM[7881]="*Iti mano anattā, dhammā anattā, manoviññāṇaṃ anattā, manosamphasso anattā, vedanā anattā, taṇhā anattā.**So the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, feeling, and craving are not self.*";
P_HTM[7882]="*Ayaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, sakkāyasamudayagāminī paṭipadā—**Now, mendicants, this is the way that leads to the origin of identity.*";
P_HTM[7883]="*cakkhuṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**You regard the eye like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’*";
P_HTM[7884]="*rūpe ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**You regard sights …*";
P_HTM[7885]="*cakkhuviññāṇaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**eye consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7886]="*cakkhusamphassaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**eye contact …*";
P_HTM[7887]="*vedanaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**feeling …*";
P_HTM[7888]="*taṇhaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati;**craving like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’*";
P_HTM[7889]="*sotaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati … pe …**You regard the ear …*";
P_HTM[7890]="*ghānaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati … pe …**nose …*";
P_HTM[7891]="*jivhaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati … pe …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[7892]="*kāyaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[7893]="*manaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati, dhamme ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati, manoviññāṇaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati, manosamphassaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati, vedanaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati, taṇhaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati.**mind … thoughts … mind consciousness … mind contact … feeling … craving like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’*";
P_HTM[7894]="*Ayaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, sakkāyanirodhagāminī paṭipadā—**But this is the way that leads to the cessation of identity.*";
P_HTM[7895]="*cakkhuṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**You regard the eye like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[7896]="*Rūpe ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**You regard sights …*";
P_HTM[7897]="*Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**eye consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7898]="*Cakkhusamphassaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**eye contact …*";
P_HTM[7899]="*Vedanaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**feeling …*";
P_HTM[7900]="*Taṇhaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**craving like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[7901]="*Sotaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati … pe …**You regard the ear …*";
P_HTM[7902]="*ghānaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati … pe …**nose …*";
P_HTM[7903]="*jivhaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati … pe …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[7904]="*kāyaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[7905]="*manaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**mind like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[7906]="*Dhamme ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**You regard thoughts …*";
P_HTM[7907]="*Manoviññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**mind consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7908]="*Manosamphassaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**mind contact …*";
P_HTM[7909]="*Vedanaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**feeling …*";
P_HTM[7910]="*Taṇhaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti samanupassati.**craving like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[7911]="*Cakkhuñca, bhikkhave, paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā.**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for the arising of what is felt as pleasant, painful, or neutral.*";
P_HTM[7912]="*So sukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**When you experience a pleasant feeling, if you approve, welcome, and keep clinging to it,*";
P_HTM[7913]="*Tassa rāgānusayo anuseti.**the underlying tendency to greed underlies that.*";
P_HTM[7914]="*Dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati.**When you experience a painful feeling, if you sorrow and wail and lament, beating your breast and falling into confusion,*";
P_HTM[7915]="*Tassa paṭighānusayo anuseti.**the underlying tendency to repulsion underlies that.*";
P_HTM[7916]="*Adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno tassā vedanāya samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**When you experience a neutral feeling, if you don’t truly understand that feeling’s origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape,*";
P_HTM[7917]="*Tassa avijjānusayo anuseti.**the underlying tendency to ignorance underlies that.*";
P_HTM[7918]="*So vata, bhikkhave, sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayaṃ appahāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayaṃ appaṭivinodetvā adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayaṃ asamūhanitvā avijjaṃ appahāya vijjaṃ anuppādetvā diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhassantakaro bhavissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**Mendicants, without giving up the underlying tendency to greed for pleasant feeling, without dispelling the underlying tendency to repulsion towards painful feeling, without eradicating ignorance in the case of neutral feeling, without giving up ignorance and without giving rise to knowledge, it’s simply impossible to make an end of suffering in the present life.*";
P_HTM[7919]="*Sotañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Ear consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7920]="*ghānañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Nose consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7921]="*jivhañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Tongue consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7922]="*kāyañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Body consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7923]="*manañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā.**Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for the arising of what is felt as pleasant, painful, or neutral.*";
P_HTM[7924]="*So sukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**When you experience a pleasant feeling, if you approve, welcome, and keep clinging to it,*";
P_HTM[7925]="*Tassa rāgānusayo anuseti.**the underlying tendency to greed underlies that.*";
P_HTM[7926]="*Dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati.**When you experience a painful feeling, if you sorrow and wail and lament, beating your breast and falling into confusion,*";
P_HTM[7927]="*Tassa paṭighānusayo anuseti.**the underlying tendency to repulsion underlies that.*";
P_HTM[7928]="*Adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno tassā vedanāya samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti.**When you experience a neutral feeling, if you don’t truly understand that feeling’s origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape,*";
P_HTM[7929]="*Tassa avijjānusayo anuseti.**the underlying tendency to ignorance underlies that.*";
P_HTM[7930]="*So vata, bhikkhave, sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayaṃ appahāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayaṃ appaṭivinodetvā adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayaṃ asamūhanitvā avijjaṃ appahāya vijjaṃ anuppādetvā diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhassantakaro bhavissatīti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**Mendicants, without giving up the underlying tendency to greed for pleasant feeling, without dispelling the underlying tendency to repulsion towards painful feeling, without eradicating ignorance in the case of neutral feeling, without giving up ignorance and without giving rise to knowledge, it’s simply impossible to make an end of suffering in the present life.*";
P_HTM[7931]="*Cakkhuñca, bhikkhave, paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā.**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for the arising of what is felt as pleasant, painful, or neutral.*";
P_HTM[7932]="*So sukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**When you experience a pleasant feeling, if you don’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to it,*";
P_HTM[7933]="*Tassa rāgānusayo nānuseti.**the underlying tendency to greed does not underlie that.*";
P_HTM[7934]="*Dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na socati na kilamati na paridevati na urattāḷiṃ kandati na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**When you experience a painful feeling, if you don’t sorrow or wail or lament, beating your breast and falling into confusion,*";
P_HTM[7935]="*Tassa paṭighānusayo nānuseti.**the underlying tendency to repulsion does not underlie that.*";
P_HTM[7936]="*Adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno tassā vedanāya samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**When you experience a neutral feeling, if you truly understand that feeling’s origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape,*";
P_HTM[7937]="*Tassa avijjānusayo nānuseti.**the underlying tendency to ignorance does not underlie that.*";
P_HTM[7938]="*So vata, bhikkhave, sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayaṃ pahāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayaṃ paṭivinodetvā adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayaṃ samūhanitvā avijjaṃ pahāya vijjaṃ uppādetvā diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhassantakaro bhavissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**Mendicants, after giving up the underlying tendency to greed for pleasant feeling, after dispelling the underlying tendency to repulsion towards painful feeling, after eradicating ignorance in the case of neutral feeling, after giving up ignorance and giving rise to knowledge, it’s totally possible to make an end of suffering in the present life.*";
P_HTM[7939]="*Sotañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ … pe ….**Ear consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7940]="*Ghānañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ … pe ….**Nose consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7941]="*Jivhañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ … pe ….**Tongue consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7942]="*Kāyañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ … pe ….**Body consciousness …*";
P_HTM[7943]="*“Manañca, bhikkhave, paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā.**Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for what is felt as pleasant, painful, or neutral.*";
P_HTM[7944]="*So sukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**When you experience a pleasant feeling, if you don’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to it,*";
P_HTM[7945]="*Tassa rāgānusayo nānuseti.**the underlying tendency to greed does not underlie that.*";
P_HTM[7946]="*Dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na socati na kilamati na paridevati na urattāḷiṃ kandati na sammohaṃ āpajjati.**When you experience a painful feeling, if you don’t sorrow or wail or lament, beating your breast and falling into confusion,*";
P_HTM[7947]="*Tassa paṭighānusayo nānuseti.**the underlying tendency to repulsion does not underlie that.*";
P_HTM[7948]="*Adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno tassā vedanāya samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti.**When you experience a neutral feeling, if you truly understand that feeling’s origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape,*";
P_HTM[7949]="*Tassa avijjānusayo nānuseti.**the underlying tendency to ignorance does not underlie that.*";
P_HTM[7950]="*So vata, bhikkhave, sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayaṃ pahāya dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayaṃ paṭivinodetvā adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayaṃ samūhanitvā avijjaṃ pahāya vijjaṃ uppādetvā diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhassantakaro bhavissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**Mendicants, after giving up the underlying tendency to greed for pleasant feeling, after dispelling the underlying tendency to repulsion towards painful feeling, after eradicating ignorance in the case of neutral feeling, after giving up ignorance and giving rise to knowledge, it’s totally possible to make an end of suffering in the present life.*";
P_HTM[7951]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmiṃ nibbindati, rūpesu nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇe nibbindati, cakkhusamphasse nibbindati, vedanāya nibbindati, taṇhāya nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, feeling, and craving.*";
P_HTM[7952]="*Sotasmiṃ nibbindati, saddesu nibbindati … pe …**They grow disillusioned with the ear …*";
P_HTM[7953]="*ghānasmiṃ nibbindati, gandhesu nibbindati …**nose …*";
P_HTM[7954]="*jivhāya nibbindati, rasesu nibbindati …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[7955]="*kāyasmiṃ nibbindati, phoṭṭhabbesu nibbindati …**body …*";
P_HTM[7956]="*manasmiṃ nibbindati, dhammesu nibbindati, manoviññāṇe nibbindati, manosamphasse nibbindati, vedanāya nibbindati, taṇhāya nibbindati.**mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, feeling, and craving.*";
P_HTM[7957]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When it is freed, they know it is freed.*";
P_HTM[7958]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[7959]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7960]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[7961]="*Imasmiṃ kho pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne saṭṭhimattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti.**And while this discourse was being spoken, the minds of sixty mendicants were freed from defilements by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[7962]="*Chachakkasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[7963]="*149. Mahāsaḷāyatanikasutta**The Great Discourse on the Six Sense Fields*";
P_HTM[7964]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[7965]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[7966]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[7967]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[7968]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7969]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7970]="*“mahāsaḷāyatanikaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I shall teach you the great discourse on the six sense fields.*";
P_HTM[7971]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[7972]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[7973]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[7974]="*“Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, rūpe ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, cakkhusamphassaṃ ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, yamidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, cakkhusmiṃ sārajjati, rūpesu sārajjati, cakkhuviññāṇe sārajjati, cakkhusamphasse sārajjati, yamidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi sārajjati.**“Mendicants, when you don’t truly know and see the eye, sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, and what is felt as pleasant, painful, or neutral that arises conditioned by eye contact, you’re aroused by desire for these things.*";
P_HTM[7975]="*Tassa sārattassa saṃyuttassa sammūḷhassa assādānupassino viharato āyatiṃ pañcupādānakkhandhā upacayaṃ gacchanti.**Someone who lives aroused like this—fettered, confused, concentrating on gratification—accumulates the five grasping aggregates for themselves in the future.*";
P_HTM[7976]="*Taṇhā cassa ponobbhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, sā cassa pavaḍḍhati.**And their craving—which leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and greed, looking for enjoyment in various different realms—grows.*";
P_HTM[7977]="*Tassa kāyikāpi darathā pavaḍḍhanti, cetasikāpi darathā pavaḍḍhanti;**Their physical and mental stress,*";
P_HTM[7978]="*kāyikāpi santāpā pavaḍḍhanti, cetasikāpi santāpā pavaḍḍhanti;**torment,*";
P_HTM[7979]="*kāyikāpi pariḷāhā pavaḍḍhanti, cetasikāpi pariḷāhā pavaḍḍhanti.**and fever grow.*";
P_HTM[7980]="*So kāyadukkhampi cetodukkhampi paṭisaṃvedeti.**And they experience physical and mental suffering.*";
P_HTM[7981]="*Sotaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ … pe …**When you don’t truly know and see the ear …*";
P_HTM[7982]="*ghānaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ … pe …**nose …*";
P_HTM[7983]="*jivhaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ … pe …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[7984]="*kāyaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[7985]="*manaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, dhamme, bhikkhave, ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, manoviññāṇaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, manosamphassaṃ, bhikkhave, ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, yamidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi ajānaṃ apassaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, manasmiṃ sārajjati, dhammesu sārajjati, manoviññāṇe sārajjati, manosamphasse sārajjati, yamidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi sārajjati.**mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, and what is felt as pleasant, painful, or neutral that arises conditioned by mind contact, you’re aroused by desire for these things.*";
P_HTM[7986]="*Tassa sārattassa saṃyuttassa sammūḷhassa assādānupassino viharato āyatiṃ pañcupādānakkhandhā upacayaṃ gacchanti.**Someone who lives aroused like this—fettered, confused, concentrating on gratification—accumulates the five grasping aggregates for themselves in the future.*";
P_HTM[7987]="*Taṇhā cassa ponobbhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, sā cassa pavaḍḍhati.**And their craving—which leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and greed, looking for enjoyment in various different realms—grows.*";
P_HTM[7988]="*Tassa kāyikāpi darathā pavaḍḍhanti, cetasikāpi darathā pavaḍḍhanti;**Their physical and mental stress,*";
P_HTM[7989]="*kāyikāpi santāpā pavaḍḍhanti, cetasikāpi santāpā pavaḍḍhanti;**torment,*";
P_HTM[7990]="*kāyikāpi pariḷāhā pavaḍḍhanti, cetasikāpi pariḷāhā pavaḍḍhanti.**and fever grow.*";
P_HTM[7991]="*So kāyadukkhampi cetodukkhampi paṭisaṃvedeti.**And they experience physical and mental suffering.*";
P_HTM[7992]="*Cakkhuñca kho, bhikkhave, jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, rūpe jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, cakkhusamphassaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, yamidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, cakkhusmiṃ na sārajjati, rūpesu na sārajjati, cakkhuviññāṇe na sārajjati, cakkhusamphasse na sārajjati, yamidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi na sārajjati.**When you do truly know and see the eye, sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, and what is felt as pleasant, painful, or neutral that arises conditioned by eye contact, you’re not aroused by desire for these things.*";
P_HTM[7993]="*Tassa asārattassa asaṃyuttassa asammūḷhassa ādīnavānupassino viharato āyatiṃ pañcupādānakkhandhā apacayaṃ gacchanti.**Someone who lives unaroused like this—unfettered, unconfused, concentrating on drawbacks—disperses the the five grasping aggregates for themselves in the future.*";
P_HTM[7994]="*Taṇhā cassa ponobbhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, sā cassa pahīyati.**And their craving—which leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and greed, looking for enjoyment in various different realms—is given up.*";
P_HTM[7995]="*Tassa kāyikāpi darathā pahīyanti, cetasikāpi darathā pahīyanti;**Their physical and mental stress,*";
P_HTM[7996]="*kāyikāpi santāpā pahīyanti, cetasikāpi santāpā pahīyanti;**torment,*";
P_HTM[7997]="*kāyikāpi pariḷāhā pahīyanti, cetasikāpi pariḷāhā pahīyanti.**and fever are given up.*";
P_HTM[7998]="*So kāyasukhampi cetosukhampi paṭisaṃvedeti.**And they experience physical and mental pleasure.*";
P_HTM[7999]="*Yā tathābhūtassa diṭṭhi sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi;**The view of such a person is right view.*";
P_HTM[8000]="*yo tathābhūtassa saṅkappo svāssa hoti sammāsaṅkappo;**Their intention is right intention,*";
P_HTM[8001]="*yo tathābhūtassa vāyāmo svāssa hoti sammāvāyāmo;**their effort is right effort,*";
P_HTM[8002]="*yā tathābhūtassa sati sāssa hoti sammāsati;**their mindfulness is right mindfulness,*";
P_HTM[8003]="*yo tathābhūtassa samādhi svāssa hoti sammāsamādhi.**and their immersion is right immersion.*";
P_HTM[8004]="*Pubbeva kho panassa kāyakammaṃ vacīkammaṃ ājīvo suparisuddho hoti.**And their actions of body and speech have already been fully purified before.*";
P_HTM[8005]="*Evamassāyaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati.**So this noble eightfold path is fully developed.*";
P_HTM[8006]="*Tassa evaṃ imaṃ ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvayato cattāropi satipaṭṭhānā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, cattāropi sammappadhānā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, cattāropi iddhipādā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, pañcapi indriyāni bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, pañcapi balāni bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, sattapi bojjhaṅgā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.**When the noble eightfold path is developed, the following are fully developed: the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, the four right efforts, the four bases of psychic power, the five faculties, the five powers, and the seven awakening factors.*";
P_HTM[8007]="*Tassime dve dhammā yuganandhā vattanti—**And these two qualities proceed in conjunction:*";
P_HTM[8008]="*samatho ca vipassanā ca.**serenity and discernment.*";
P_HTM[8009]="*So ye dhammā abhiññā pariññeyyā te dhamme abhiññā parijānāti.**They completely understand by direct knowledge those things that should be completely understood by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[8010]="*Ye dhammā abhiññā pahātabbā te dhamme abhiññā pajahati.**They give up by direct knowledge those things that should be given up by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[8011]="*Ye dhammā abhiññā bhāvetabbā te dhamme abhiññā bhāveti.**They develop by direct knowledge those things that should be developed by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[8012]="*Ye dhammā abhiññā sacchikātabbā te dhamme abhiññā sacchikaroti.**They realize by direct knowledge those things that should be realized by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[8013]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pariññeyyā?**And what are the things that should be completely understood by direct knowledge?*";
P_HTM[8014]="*‘Pañcupādānakkhandhā’ tissa vacanīyaṃ,**You should say: ‘The five grasping aggregates.’*";
P_HTM[8015]="*seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho.**That is: form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness.*";
P_HTM[8016]="*Ime dhammā abhiññā pariññeyyā.**These are the things that should be completely understood by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[8017]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pahātabbā?**And what are the things that should be given up by direct knowledge?*";
P_HTM[8018]="*Avijjā ca bhavataṇhā ca—**Ignorance and craving for continued existence.*";
P_HTM[8019]="*ime dhammā abhiññā pahātabbā.**These are the things that should be given up by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[8020]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā bhāvetabbā?**And what are the things that should be developed by direct knowledge?*";
P_HTM[8021]="*Samatho ca vipassanā ca—**Serenity and discernment.*";
P_HTM[8022]="*ime dhammā abhiññā bhāvetabbā.**These are the things that should be developed by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[8023]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā sacchikātabbā?**And what are the things that should be realized by direct knowledge?*";
P_HTM[8024]="*Vijjā ca vimutti ca—**Knowledge and freedom.*";
P_HTM[8025]="*ime dhammā abhiññā sacchikātabbā.**These are the things that should be realized by direct knowledge.*";
P_HTM[8026]="*Sotaṃ, bhikkhave, jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ … pe …**When you truly know and see the ear …*";
P_HTM[8027]="*ghānaṃ bhikkhave, jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ … pe …**nose …*";
P_HTM[8028]="*jivhaṃ, bhikkhave, jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ … pe …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[8029]="*kāyaṃ, bhikkhave, jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[8030]="*manaṃ, bhikkhave, jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, dhamme jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, manoviññāṇaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, manosamphassaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, yamidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi jānaṃ passaṃ yathābhūtaṃ, manasmiṃ na sārajjati, dhammesu na sārajjati, manoviññāṇe na sārajjati, manosamphasse na sārajjati, yamidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi na sārajjati.**mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, and what is felt as pleasant, painful, or neutral that arises conditioned by mind contact, you are not aroused by desire for these things. …*";
P_HTM[8031]="*Tassa asārattassa asaṃyuttassa asammūḷhassa ādīnavānupassino viharato āyatiṃ pañcupādānakkhandhā apacayaṃ gacchanti.* **";
P_HTM[8032]="*Taṇhā cassa ponobbhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, sā cassa pahīyati.* **";
P_HTM[8033]="*Tassa kāyikāpi darathā pahīyanti, cetasikāpi darathā pahīyanti;* **";
P_HTM[8034]="*kāyikāpi santāpā pahīyanti, cetasikāpi santāpā pahīyanti;* **";
P_HTM[8035]="*kāyikāpi pariḷāhā pahīyanti, cetasikāpi pariḷāhā pahīyanti.* **";
P_HTM[8036]="*So kāyasukhampi cetosukhampi paṭisaṃvedeti.* **";
P_HTM[8037]="*Yā tathābhūtassa diṭṭhi sāssa hoti sammādiṭṭhi;* **";
P_HTM[8038]="*yo tathābhūtassa saṅkappo svāssa hoti sammāsaṅkappo;* **";
P_HTM[8039]="*yo tathābhūtassa vāyāmo svāssa hoti sammāvāyāmo;* **";
P_HTM[8040]="*yā tathābhūtassa sati sāssa hoti sammāsati;* **";
P_HTM[8041]="*yo tathābhūtassa samādhi svāssa hoti sammāsamādhi.* **";
P_HTM[8042]="*Pubbeva kho panassa kāyakammaṃ vacīkammaṃ ājīvo suparisuddho hoti.* **";
P_HTM[8043]="*Evamassāyaṃ ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchati.* **";
P_HTM[8044]="*Tassa evaṃ imaṃ ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvayato cattāropi satipaṭṭhānā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, cattāropi sammappadhānā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, cattāropi iddhipādā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, pañcapi indriyāni bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, pañcapi balāni bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti, sattapi bojjhaṅgā bhāvanāpāripūriṃ gacchanti.* **";
P_HTM[8045]="*Tassime dve dhammā yuganandhā vattanti—* **";
P_HTM[8046]="*samatho ca vipassanā ca.* **";
P_HTM[8047]="*So ye dhammā abhiññā pariññeyyā te dhamme abhiññā parijānāti.* **";
P_HTM[8048]="*Ye dhammā abhiññā pahātabbā te dhamme abhiññā pajahati.* **";
P_HTM[8049]="*Ye dhammā abhiññā bhāvetabbā te dhamme abhiññā bhāveti.* **";
P_HTM[8050]="*Ye dhammā abhiññā sacchikātabbā te dhamme abhiññā sacchikaroti.* **";
P_HTM[8051]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pariññeyyā?* **";
P_HTM[8052]="*‘Pañcupādānakkhandhā’ tissa vacanīyaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—* **";
P_HTM[8053]="*rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho.* **";
P_HTM[8054]="*Ime dhammā abhiññā pariññeyyā.* **";
P_HTM[8055]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā pahātabbā?* **";
P_HTM[8056]="*Avijjā ca bhavataṇhā ca—* **";
P_HTM[8057]="*ime dhammā abhiññā pahātabbā.* **";
P_HTM[8058]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā bhāvetabbā?* **";
P_HTM[8059]="*Samatho ca vipassanā ca—* **";
P_HTM[8060]="*ime dhammā abhiññā bhāvetabbā.* **";
P_HTM[8061]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, dhammā abhiññā sacchikātabbā?* **";
P_HTM[8062]="*Vijjā ca vimutti ca—* **";
P_HTM[8063]="*ime dhammā abhiññā sacchikātabbā”ti.**These are the things that should be realized by direct knowledge.”*";
P_HTM[8064]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8065]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8066]="*Mahāsaḷāyatanikasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8067]="*150. Nagaravindeyyasutta**With the People of Nagaravinda*";
P_HTM[8068]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8069]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena nagaravindaṃ nāma kosalānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ gāmo tadavasari.**At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a village of the Kosalan brahmins named Nagaravinda.*";
P_HTM[8070]="*Assosuṃ kho nagaravindeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā:**The brahmins and householders of Nagaravinda heard,*";
P_HTM[8071]="*“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ nagaravindaṃ anuppatto.**“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—while wandering in the land of the Kosalans has arrived at Nagaravinda, together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants.*";
P_HTM[8072]="*Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato:**He has this good reputation:*";
P_HTM[8073]="*‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
P_HTM[8074]="*So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti.**He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others.*";
P_HTM[8075]="*So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti.**He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.*";
P_HTM[8076]="*Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti.**It’s good to see such perfected ones.”*";
P_HTM[8077]="*Atha kho nagaravindeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā appekacce bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu; sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce bhagavato santike nāmagottaṃ sāvetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Appekacce tuṇhībhūtā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho nagaravindeyyake brāhmaṇagahapatike bhagavā etadavoca:**Then the brahmins and householders of Nagaravinda went up to the Buddha. Before sitting down to one side, some bowed, some exchanged greetings and polite conversation, some held up their joined palms toward the Buddha, some announced their name and clan, while some kept silent. The Buddha said to them:*";
P_HTM[8078]="*“Sace vo, gahapatayo, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**“Householders, if wanderers who follow another path were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[8079]="*‘kathaṃbhūtā, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā’ti?**‘What kind of ascetic or brahmin doesn’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration?’*";
P_HTM[8080]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**You should answer them:*";
P_HTM[8081]="*‘ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā, ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ caranti kāyena vācāya manasā, evarūpā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā.**‘There are ascetics and brahmins who are not free of greed, hate, and delusion for sights known by the eye, who are not peaceful inside, and who conduct themselves badly among the good by way of body, speech, and mind. They don’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration.*";
P_HTM[8082]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[8083]="*Mayampi hi cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā, ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ carāma kāyena vācāya manasā, tesaṃ no samacariyampi hetaṃ uttari apassataṃ.**Because we ourselves are not free of these things, so we do not see that they have any higher good conduct than us.*";
P_HTM[8084]="*Tasmā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā.**That’s why they don’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration.*";
P_HTM[8085]="*Ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sotaviññeyyesu saddesu …**There are ascetics and brahmins who are not free of greed, hate, and delusion for sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[8086]="*ghānaviññeyyesu gandhesu …**smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[8087]="*jivhāviññeyyesu rasesu …**tastes known by the tongue…*";
P_HTM[8088]="*kāyaviññeyyesu phoṭṭhabbesu …**touches known by the body …*";
P_HTM[8089]="*manoviññeyyesu dhammesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā, ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ caranti kāyena vācāya manasā, evarūpā samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā.**thoughts known by the mind, who are not peaceful inside, and who conduct themselves badly among the good by way of body, speech, and mind. They don’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration.*";
P_HTM[8090]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[8091]="*Mayampi hi manoviññeyyesu dhammesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā, ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ carāma kāyena vācāya manasā, tesaṃ no samacariyampi hetaṃ uttari apassataṃ.**Because we ourselves are not free of these things, so we do not see that they have any higher good conduct than us.*";
P_HTM[8092]="*Tasmā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā na sakkātabbā na garukātabbā na mānetabbā na pūjetabbā’ti.**That’s why they don’t deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration.’*";
P_HTM[8093]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha.**When questioned by wanderers who follow other paths, that’s how you should answer them.*";
P_HTM[8094]="*Sace pana vo, gahapatayo, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**If wanderers who follow other paths were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[8095]="*‘kathaṃbhūtā, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇā sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā’ti?**‘What kind of ascetic or brahmin deserves honor, respect, reverence, and veneration?’*";
P_HTM[8096]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**You should answer them:*";
P_HTM[8097]="*‘ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu vītarāgā vītadosā vītamohā, ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacittā, samacariyaṃ caranti kāyena vācāya manasā, evarūpā samaṇabrāhmaṇā sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā.**‘There are ascetics and brahmins who are free of greed, hate, and delusion for sights known by the eye, who are peaceful inside, and who conduct themselves well by way of body, speech, and mind. They deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration.*";
P_HTM[8098]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[8099]="*Mayampi hi cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā, ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ carāma kāyena vācāya manasā, tesaṃ no samacariyampi hetaṃ uttari passataṃ.**Because we ourselves are not free of these things, but we see that they have a higher good conduct than us.*";
P_HTM[8100]="*Tasmā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā.**That’s why they deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration.*";
P_HTM[8101]="*Ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sotaviññeyyesu saddesu …**There are ascetics and brahmins who are free of greed, hate, and delusion for sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[8102]="*ghānaviññeyyesu gandhesu …**smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[8103]="*jivhāviññeyyesu rasesu …**tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[8104]="*kāyaviññeyyesu phoṭṭhabbesu …**touches known by the body …*";
P_HTM[8105]="*manoviññeyyesu dhammesu vītarāgā vītadosā vītamohā, ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacittā, samacariyaṃ caranti kāyena vācāya manasā, evarūpā samaṇabrāhmaṇā sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā.**thoughts known by the mind, who are peaceful inside, and who conduct themselves well by way of body, speech, and mind. They deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration.*";
P_HTM[8106]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[8107]="*Mayampi hi manoviññeyyesu dhammesu avītarāgā avītadosā avītamohā ajjhattaṃ avūpasantacittā, samavisamaṃ carāma kāyena vācāya manasā, tesaṃ no samacariyampi hetaṃ uttari passataṃ.**Because we ourselves are not free of these things, but we see that they have a higher good conduct than us.*";
P_HTM[8108]="*Tasmā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā sakkātabbā garukātabbā mānetabbā pūjetabbā’ti.**That’s why they deserve honor, respect, reverence, and veneration.*";
P_HTM[8109]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha.**When questioned by wanderers who follow other paths, that’s how you should answer them.*";
P_HTM[8110]="*Sace pana vo, gahapatayo, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:**If wanderers who follow other paths were to ask you:*";
P_HTM[8111]="*‘ke panāyasmantānaṃ ākārā, ke anvayā, yena tumhe āyasmanto evaṃ vadetha?**‘But what reasons and evidence do you have regarding those venerables that justifies saying,*";
P_HTM[8112]="*Addhā te āyasmanto vītarāgā vā rāgavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītadosā vā dosavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītamohā vā mohavinayāya vā paṭipannā’ti?**“Clearly those venerables are free of greed, hate, and delusion, or practicing to be free of them”?’*";
P_HTM[8113]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyātha:**You should answer them:*";
P_HTM[8114]="*‘tathā hi te āyasmanto araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti.**‘It’s because those venerables frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.*";
P_HTM[8115]="*Natthi kho pana tattha tathārūpā cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā ye disvā disvā abhirameyyuṃ, natthi kho pana tattha tathārūpā sotaviññeyyā saddā ye sutvā sutvā abhirameyyuṃ, natthi kho pana tattha tathārūpā ghānaviññeyyā gandhā ye ghāyitvā ghāyitvā abhirameyyuṃ, natthi kho pana tattha tathārūpā jivhāviññeyyā rasā ye sāyitvā sāyitvā abhirameyyuṃ, natthi kho pana tattha tathārūpā kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā ye phusitvā phusitvā abhirameyyuṃ.**In such places there are no sights known by the eye to see and enjoy, there are no sounds known by the ear to hear and enjoy, no odors known by the nose to smell and enjoy, no flavors known by the tongue to taste and enjoy, and no touches known by the body to feel and enjoy.*";
P_HTM[8116]="*Ime kho no, āvuso, ākārā, ime anvayā, yena mayaṃ evaṃ vadema—**These are the reasons and evidence that you have regarding those venerables that justifies saying,*";
P_HTM[8117]="*addhā te āyasmanto vītarāgā vā rāgavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītadosā vā dosavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītamohā vā mohavinayāya vā paṭipannā’ti.**“Clearly those venerables are free of greed, hate, and delusion, or practicing to be free of them”.’*";
P_HTM[8118]="*Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, gahapatayo, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ byākareyyāthā”ti.**When questioned by wanderers who follow other paths, that’s how you should answer them.”*";
P_HTM[8119]="*Evaṃ vutte, nagaravindeyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When he had spoken, the brahmins and householders of Nagaravinda said to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[8120]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama.**“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[8121]="*Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the Teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[8122]="*Ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[8123]="*Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupete saraṇaṃ gate”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[8124]="*Nagaravindeyyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8125]="*151. Piṇḍapātapārisuddhisutta**The Purification of Alms*";
P_HTM[8126]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8127]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[8128]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta came out of retreat and went to the Buddha. He bowed and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[8129]="*“Vippasannāni kho te, sāriputta, indriyāni, parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto.**“Sāriputta, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright.*";
P_HTM[8130]="*Katamena kho tvaṃ, sāriputta, vihārena etarahi bahulaṃ viharasī”ti?**What kind of meditation are you usually practicing these days?”*";
P_HTM[8131]="*“Suññatāvihārena kho ahaṃ, bhante, etarahi bahulaṃ viharāmī”ti.**“Sir, these days I usually practice the meditation on emptiness.”*";
P_HTM[8132]="*“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta.**“Good, good, Sāriputta!*";
P_HTM[8133]="*Mahāpurisavihārena kira tvaṃ, sāriputta, etarahi bahulaṃ viharasi.**It seems you usually practice the meditation of a great man.*";
P_HTM[8134]="*Mahāpurisavihāro eso, sāriputta, yadidaṃ—**For emptiness is the meditation of a great man.*";
P_HTM[8135]="*suññatā.* **";
P_HTM[8136]="*Tasmātiha, sāriputta, bhikkhu sace ākaṅkheyya:**Now, a mendicant might wish:*";
P_HTM[8137]="*‘suññatāvihārena bahulaṃ vihareyyan’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**‘May I usually practice the meditation on emptiness.’ So they should reflect:*";
P_HTM[8138]="*‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, atthi nu kho me tattha cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti?**‘Along the path that I went for alms, or in the place I wandered for alms, or along the path that I returned from alms, was there any desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in my heart for sights known by the eye?’*";
P_HTM[8139]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8140]="*‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, atthi me tattha cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**there was such desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in their heart, they should make an effort to give up those unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8141]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8142]="*‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, natthi me tattha cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**there was no such desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in their heart, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8143]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**Furthermore, a mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[8144]="*‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, atthi nu kho me tattha sotaviññeyyesu saddesu … pe …**‘Along the path that I went for alms, or in the place I wandered for alms, or along the path that I returned from alms, was there any desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in my heart for sounds known by the ear …*";
P_HTM[8145]="*ghānaviññeyyesu gandhesu …**smells known by the nose …*";
P_HTM[8146]="*jivhāviññeyyesu rasesu …**tastes known by the tongue …*";
P_HTM[8147]="*kāyaviññeyyesu phoṭṭhabbesu …**touches known by the body …*";
P_HTM[8148]="*manoviññeyyesu dhammesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti?**thoughts known by the mind?’*";
P_HTM[8149]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8150]="*‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, atthi me tattha manoviññeyyesu dhammesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**there was such desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in their heart, they should make an effort to give up those unskillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8151]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8152]="*‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, natthi me tattha manoviññeyyesu dhammesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**there was no such desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in their heart, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8153]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**Furthermore, a mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[8154]="*‘pahīnā nu kho me pañca kāmaguṇā’ti?**‘Have I given up the five kinds of sensual stimulation?’*";
P_HTM[8155]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8156]="*‘appahīnā kho me pañca kāmaguṇā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā pañcannaṃ kāmaguṇānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**they have not given them up, they should make an effort to do so.*";
P_HTM[8157]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8158]="*‘pahīnā kho me pañca kāmaguṇā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**they have given them up, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8159]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**Furthermore, a mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[8160]="*‘pahīnā nu kho me pañca nīvaraṇā’ti?**‘Have I given up the five hindrances?’*";
P_HTM[8161]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8162]="*‘appahīnā kho me pañca nīvaraṇā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā pañcannaṃ nīvaraṇānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**they have not given them up, they should make an effort to do so.*";
P_HTM[8163]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8164]="*‘pahīnā kho me pañca nīvaraṇā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**they have given them up, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8165]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**Furthermore, a mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[8166]="*‘pariññātā nu kho me pañcupādānakkhandhā’ti?**‘Have I completely understood the five grasping aggregates?’*";
P_HTM[8167]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8168]="*‘apariññātā kho me pañcupādānakkhandhā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ pariññāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**they have not completely understood them, they should make an effort to do so.*";
P_HTM[8169]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8170]="*‘pariññātā kho me pañcupādānakkhandhā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**they have completely understood them, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8171]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**Furthermore, a mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[8172]="*‘bhāvitā nu kho me cattāro satipaṭṭhānā’ti?**‘Have I developed the four kinds of mindfulness meditation?’*";
P_HTM[8173]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8174]="*‘abhāvitā kho me cattāro satipaṭṭhānā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvanāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**they haven’t developed them, they should make an effort to do so.*";
P_HTM[8175]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8176]="*‘bhāvitā kho me cattāro satipaṭṭhānā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**they have developed them, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8177]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**Furthermore, a mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[8178]="*‘bhāvitā nu kho me cattāro sammappadhānā’ti?**‘Have I developed the four right efforts …*";
P_HTM[8179]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8180]="*‘abhāvitā kho me cattāro sammappadhānā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā catunnaṃ sammappadhānānaṃ bhāvanāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8181]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8182]="*‘bhāvitā kho me cattāro sammappadhānā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.* **";
P_HTM[8183]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[8184]="*‘bhāvitā nu kho me cattāro iddhipādā’ti?**the four bases of psychic power …*";
P_HTM[8185]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8186]="*‘abhāvitā kho me cattāro iddhipādā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvanāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8187]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8188]="*‘bhāvitā kho me cattāro iddhipādā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.* **";
P_HTM[8189]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[8190]="*‘bhāvitāni nu kho me pañcindriyānī’ti?**the five faculties …*";
P_HTM[8191]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8192]="*‘abhāvitāni kho me pañcindriyānī’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ bhāvanāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8193]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8194]="*‘bhāvitāni kho me pañcindriyānī’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.* **";
P_HTM[8195]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[8196]="*‘bhāvitāni nu kho me pañca balānī’ti?**the five powers …*";
P_HTM[8197]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8198]="*‘abhāvitāni kho me pañca balānī’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā pañcannaṃ balānaṃ bhāvanāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8199]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8200]="*‘bhāvitāni kho me pañca balānī’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.* **";
P_HTM[8201]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[8202]="*‘bhāvitā nu kho me satta bojjhaṅgā’ti?**the seven awakening factors …*";
P_HTM[8203]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8204]="*‘abhāvitā kho me satta bojjhaṅgā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā sattannaṃ bojjhaṅgānaṃ bhāvanāya vāyamitabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8205]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:* **";
P_HTM[8206]="*‘bhāvitā kho me satta bojjhaṅgā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.* **";
P_HTM[8207]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:* **";
P_HTM[8208]="*‘bhāvito nu kho me ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo’ti?**the noble eightfold path?’*";
P_HTM[8209]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8210]="*‘abhāvito kho me ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā ariyassa aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa bhāvanāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**they haven’t developed it, they should make an effort to do so.*";
P_HTM[8211]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8212]="*‘bhāvito kho me ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**they have developed it, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8213]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**Furthermore, a mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[8214]="*‘bhāvitā nu kho me samatho ca vipassanā cā’ti?**‘Have I developed serenity and discernment?’*";
P_HTM[8215]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8216]="*‘abhāvitā kho me samatho ca vipassanā cā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā samathavipassanānaṃ bhāvanāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**they haven’t developed them, they should make an effort to do so.*";
P_HTM[8217]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8218]="*‘bhāvitā kho me samatho ca vipassanā cā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**they have developed them, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8219]="*Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ:**Furthermore, a mendicant should reflect:*";
P_HTM[8220]="*‘sacchikatā nu kho me vijjā ca vimutti cā’ti?**‘Have I realized knowledge and freedom?’*";
P_HTM[8221]="*Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8222]="*‘asacchikatā kho me vijjā ca vimutti cā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā vijjāya vimuttiyā sacchikiriyāya vāyamitabbaṃ.**they haven’t realized them, they should make an effort to do so.*";
P_HTM[8223]="*Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti:**But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that*";
P_HTM[8224]="*‘sacchikatā kho me vijjā ca vimutti cā’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu.**they have realized them, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities.*";
P_HTM[8225]="*Ye hi keci, sāriputta, atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā piṇḍapātaṃ parisodhesuṃ, sabbe te evameva paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā piṇḍapātaṃ parisodhesuṃ.**Whether in the past, future, or present, all those who purify their alms-food do so by continually checking in this way.*";
P_HTM[8226]="*Yepi hi keci, sāriputta, anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā piṇḍapātaṃ parisodhessanti, sabbe te evameva paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā piṇḍapātaṃ parisodhessanti.* **";
P_HTM[8227]="*Yepi hi keci, sāriputta, etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā piṇḍapātaṃ parisodhenti, sabbe te evameva paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā piṇḍapātaṃ parisodhenti.* **";
P_HTM[8228]="*Tasmātiha, sāriputta, ‘paccavekkhitvā paccavekkhitvā piṇḍapātaṃ parisodhessāmā’ti—**So, Sāriputta, you should all train like this: ‘We shall purify our alms-food by continually checking.’”*";
P_HTM[8229]="*evañhi vo, sāriputta, sikkhitabban”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8230]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8231]="*Attamano āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Sāriputta was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8232]="*Piṇḍapātapārisuddhisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8233]="*152. Indriyabhāvanāsutta**The Development of the Faculties*";
P_HTM[8234]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8235]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā gajaṅgalāyaṃ viharati suveḷuvane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Kajaṅgalā in a bamboo grove.*";
P_HTM[8236]="*Atha kho uttaro māṇavo pārāsiviyantevāsī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the brahmin student Uttara, a pupil of the brahmin Pārāsariya, approached the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[8237]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho uttaraṃ māṇavaṃ pārāsiviyantevāsiṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him,*";
P_HTM[8238]="*“deseti, uttara, pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ indriyabhāvanan”ti?**“Uttara, does Pārāsariya teach his disciples the development of the faculties?”*";
P_HTM[8239]="*“Deseti, bho gotama, pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ indriyabhāvanan”ti.**“He does, Master Gotama.”*";
P_HTM[8240]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana, uttara, deseti pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ indriyabhāvanan”ti?**“But how does he teach it?”*";
P_HTM[8241]="*“Idha, bho gotama, cakkhunā rūpaṃ na passati, sotena saddaṃ na suṇāti—**“Master Gotama, it’s when the eye sees no sight and the ear hears no sound.*";
P_HTM[8242]="*evaṃ kho, bho gotama, deseti pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ indriyabhāvanan”ti.**That’s how Pārāsariya teaches his disciples the development of the faculties.”*";
P_HTM[8243]="*“Evaṃ sante kho, uttara, andho bhāvitindriyo bhavissati, badhiro bhāvitindriyo bhavissati;**“In that case, Uttara, a blind person and a deaf person will have developed faculties*";
P_HTM[8244]="*yathā pārāsiviyassa brāhmaṇassa vacanaṃ.**according to what Pārāsariya says.*";
P_HTM[8245]="*Andho hi, uttara, cakkhunā rūpaṃ na passati, badhiro sotena saddaṃ na suṇātī”ti.**For a blind person sees no sight with the eye and a deaf person hears no sound with the ear.”*";
P_HTM[8246]="*Evaṃ vutte, uttaro māṇavo pārāsiviyantevāsī tuṇhībhūto maṅkubhūto pattakkhandho adhomukho pajjhāyanto appaṭibhāno nisīdi.**When he said this, Uttara sat silent, embarrassed, shoulders drooping, downcast, depressed, with nothing to say.*";
P_HTM[8247]="*Atha kho bhagavā uttaraṃ māṇavaṃ pārāsiviyantevāsiṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ maṅkubhūtaṃ pattakkhandhaṃ adhomukhaṃ pajjhāyantaṃ appaṭibhānaṃ viditvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:**Knowing this, the Buddha addressed Venerable Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[8248]="*“aññathā kho, ānanda, deseti pārāsiviyo brāhmaṇo sāvakānaṃ indriyabhāvanaṃ, aññathā ca panānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā hotī”ti.**“Ānanda, the development of the faculties taught by Pārāsariya is quite different from the supreme development of the faculties in the training of the noble one.”*";
P_HTM[8249]="*“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo; etassa, sugata, kālo**“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One.*";
P_HTM[8250]="*yaṃ bhagavā ariyassa vinaye anuttaraṃ indriyabhāvanaṃ deseyya. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti.**Let the Buddha teach the supreme development of the faculties in the training of the noble one. The mendicants will listen and remember it.”*";
P_HTM[8251]="*“Tenahānanda, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Well then, Ānanda, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[8252]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi.**“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied.*";
P_HTM[8253]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[8254]="*“Kathañcānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā hoti?**“And how, Ānanda, is there the supreme development of the faculties in the training of the noble one?*";
P_HTM[8255]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8256]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[8257]="*‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ manāpaṃ, uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ, uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ.**‘Liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking have come up in me.*";
P_HTM[8258]="*Tañca kho saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ.**That’s conditioned, coarse, and dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[8259]="*Etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ—**But this is peaceful and sublime, namely*";
P_HTM[8260]="*upekkhā’ti.**equanimity.’*";
P_HTM[8261]="*Tassa taṃ uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati;**Then the liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking that came up in them cease,*";
P_HTM[8262]="*upekkhā saṇṭhāti.**and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8263]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, cakkhumā puriso ummīletvā vā nimīleyya, nimīletvā vā ummīleyya;**It’s like how a person with good sight might open their eyes then shut them; or might shut their eyes then open them.*";
P_HTM[8264]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, upekkhā saṇṭhāti—**Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8265]="*ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu.**In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding sights known by the eye.*";
P_HTM[8266]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno sotena saddaṃ sutvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**Furthermore, when a mendicant hears a sound with their ears, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8267]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[8268]="*‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ manāpaṃ, uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ, uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ.**‘Liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking have come up in me.*";
P_HTM[8269]="*Tañca kho saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ.**That’s conditioned, coarse, and dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[8270]="*Etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ—**But this is peaceful and sublime, namely*";
P_HTM[8271]="*upekkhā’ti.**equanimity.’*";
P_HTM[8272]="*Tassa taṃ uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati;**Then the liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking that came up in them cease,*";
P_HTM[8273]="*upekkhā saṇṭhāti.**and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8274]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, balavā puriso appakasireneva accharaṃ pahareyya;**It’s like how a strong person can effortlessly snap their fingers.*";
P_HTM[8275]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, upekkhā saṇṭhāti—**Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8276]="*ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā sotaviññeyyesu saddesu.**In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding sounds known by the ear.*";
P_HTM[8277]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**Furthermore, when a mendicant smells an odor with their nose, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8278]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[8279]="*‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ manāpaṃ, uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ, uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ.**‘Liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking have come up in me.*";
P_HTM[8280]="*Tañca kho saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ.**That’s conditioned, coarse, and dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[8281]="*Etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ—**But this is peaceful and sublime, namely*";
P_HTM[8282]="*upekkhā’ti.**equanimity.’*";
P_HTM[8283]="*Tassa taṃ uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati;**Then the liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking that came up in them cease,*";
P_HTM[8284]="*upekkhā saṇṭhāti.**and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8285]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, īsakampoṇe padumapalāse udakaphusitāni pavattanti, na saṇṭhanti;**It’s like how a drop of water would roll off a gently sloping lotus leaf, and would not stay there.*";
P_HTM[8286]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, upekkhā saṇṭhāti—**Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8287]="*ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā ghānaviññeyyesu gandhesu.**In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding smells known by the nose.*";
P_HTM[8288]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**Furthermore, when a mendicant tastes a flavor with their tongue, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8289]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[8290]="*‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ manāpaṃ, uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ, uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ.**‘Liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking have come up in me.*";
P_HTM[8291]="*Tañca kho saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ.**That’s conditioned, coarse, and dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[8292]="*Etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ—**But this is peaceful and sublime, namely*";
P_HTM[8293]="*upekkhā’ti.**equanimity.’*";
P_HTM[8294]="*Tassa taṃ uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati;**Then the liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking that came up in them cease,*";
P_HTM[8295]="*upekkhā saṇṭhāti.**and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8296]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, balavā puriso jivhagge kheḷapiṇḍaṃ saṃyūhitvā appakasirena vameyya;**It’s like how a strong person who’s formed a glob of spit on the tip of their tongue could easily spit it out.*";
P_HTM[8297]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, upekkhā saṇṭhāti—**Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8298]="*ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā jivhāviññeyyesu rasesu.**In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding tastes known by the tongue.*";
P_HTM[8299]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**Furthermore, when a mendicant feels a touch with their body, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8300]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[8301]="*‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ manāpaṃ, uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ, uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ.**‘Liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking have come up in me.*";
P_HTM[8302]="*Tañca kho saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ.**That’s conditioned, coarse, and dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[8303]="*Etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ—**But this is peaceful and sublime, namely*";
P_HTM[8304]="*upekkhā’ti.**equanimity.’*";
P_HTM[8305]="*Tassa taṃ uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati;**Then the liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking that came up in them cease,*";
P_HTM[8306]="*upekkhā saṇṭhāti.**and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8307]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya;**It’s like how a strong person can extend or contract their arm.*";
P_HTM[8308]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, upekkhā saṇṭhāti—**Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8309]="*ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā kāyaviññeyyesu phoṭṭhabbesu.**In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding touches known by the body.*";
P_HTM[8310]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**Furthermore, when a mendicant knows a thought with their mind, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8311]="*So evaṃ pajānāti:**They understand:*";
P_HTM[8312]="*‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ manāpaṃ, uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ, uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ.**‘Liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking have come up in me.*";
P_HTM[8313]="*Tañca kho saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ.**That’s conditioned, coarse, and dependently originated.*";
P_HTM[8314]="*Etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ—**But this is peaceful and sublime, namely*";
P_HTM[8315]="*upekkhā’ti.**equanimity.’*";
P_HTM[8316]="*Tassa taṃ uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati;**Then the liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking that came up in them cease,*";
P_HTM[8317]="*upekkhā saṇṭhāti.**and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8318]="*Seyyathāpi, ānanda, balavā puriso divasaṃsantatte ayokaṭāhe dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni nipāteyya.**It’s like how a strong person could let two or three drops of water fall onto an iron cauldron that had been heated all day.*";
P_HTM[8319]="*Dandho, ānanda, udakaphusitānaṃ nipāto, atha kho naṃ khippameva parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya;**The drops would be slow to fall, but they’d quickly dry up and evaporate.*";
P_HTM[8320]="*evameva kho, ānanda, yassa kassaci evaṃsīghaṃ evaṃtuvaṭaṃ evaṃappakasirena uppannaṃ manāpaṃ uppannaṃ amanāpaṃ uppannaṃ manāpāmanāpaṃ nirujjhati, upekkhā saṇṭhāti—**Such is the speed, the swiftness, the ease with which any liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking at all that came up in them cease, and equanimity becomes stabilized.*";
P_HTM[8321]="*ayaṃ vuccatānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā manoviññeyyesu dhammesu.**In the training of the noble one this is called the supreme development of the faculties regarding thoughts known by the mind.*";
P_HTM[8322]="*Evaṃ kho, ānanda, ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā hoti.**That’s how there is the supreme development of the faculties in the training of the noble one.*";
P_HTM[8323]="*Kathañcānanda, sekho hoti pāṭipado?**And how are they a practicing trainee?*";
P_HTM[8324]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8325]="*So tena uppannena manāpena uppannena amanāpena uppannena manāpāmanāpena aṭṭīyati harāyati jigucchati.**They are horrified, repelled, and disgusted by that.*";
P_HTM[8326]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[8327]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[8328]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[8329]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[8330]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**When they know a thought with their mind, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8331]="*So tena uppannena manāpena uppannena amanāpena uppannena manāpāmanāpena aṭṭīyati harāyati jigucchati.**They are horrified, repelled, and disgusted by that.*";
P_HTM[8332]="*Evaṃ kho, ānanda, sekho hoti pāṭipado.**That’s how they are a practicing trainee.*";
P_HTM[8333]="*Kathañcānanda, ariyo hoti bhāvitindriyo?**And how are they a noble one with developed faculties?*";
P_HTM[8334]="*Idhānanda, bhikkhuno cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8335]="*So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8336]="*Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8337]="*Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8338]="*Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive and the repulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8339]="*Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ sato sampajāno’ti, upekkhako tattha viharati sato sampajāno.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8340]="*Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When they hear a sound with their ear …*";
P_HTM[8341]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[8342]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[8343]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[8344]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya uppajjati manāpaṃ, uppajjati amanāpaṃ, uppajjati manāpāmanāpaṃ.**When they know a thought with their mind, liking, disliking, and both liking and disliking come up in them.*";
P_HTM[8345]="*So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8346]="*Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8347]="*Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8348]="*Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘appaṭikūle ca paṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive and the repulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8349]="*Sace ākaṅkhati: ‘paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca tadubhayampi abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ sato sampajāno’ti, upekkhako tattha viharati sato sampajāno.**If they wish: ‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do.*";
P_HTM[8350]="*Evaṃ kho, ānanda, ariyo hoti bhāvitindriyo.**That’s how they are a noble one with developed faculties.*";
P_HTM[8351]="*Iti kho, ānanda, desitā mayā ariyassa vinaye anuttarā indriyabhāvanā, desito sekho pāṭipado, desito ariyo bhāvitindriyo.**So, Ānanda, I have taught the supreme development of the faculties in the training of the noble one, I have taught the practicing trainee, and I have taught the noble one with developed faculties.*";
P_HTM[8352]="*Yaṃ kho, ānanda, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā.**Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best for their disciples.*";
P_HTM[8353]="*Etāni, ānanda, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni, jhāyathānanda, mā pamādattha, mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti.**Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice absorption, Ānanda! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my instruction to you.”*";
P_HTM[8354]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8355]="*Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti.**Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[8356]="*Indriyabhāvanāsuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8357]="*Saḷāyatanavaggo niṭṭhito pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[8358]="*Anāthapiṇḍiko channo,* **";
P_HTM[8359]="*puṇṇo nandakarāhulā;* **";
P_HTM[8360]="*Chachakkaṃ saḷāyatanikaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[8361]="*nagaravindeyyasuddhikā;* **";
P_HTM[8362]="*Indriyabhāvanā cāpi,* **";
P_HTM[8363]="*vaggo ovādapañcamoti.* **";
P_HTM[8364]="*Devadahonupado ca,* **";
P_HTM[8365]="*Suññato ca vibhaṅgako;* **";
P_HTM[8366]="*Saḷāyatanoti vaggā,* **";
P_HTM[8367]="*Uparipaṇṇāsake ṭhitāti.* **";
P_HTM[8368]="*Uparipaṇṇāsakaṃ samattaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8369]="*Tīhi paṇṇāsakehi paṭimaṇḍito sakalo* **";
P_HTM[8370]="*majjhimanikāyo samatto.**The Middle Discourses is completed.*";
